Engineer Muhammad Nura Khalil has been declared the winner of the New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP), Governorship ticket in Katsina State. Khalil polled 950 votes to defeat his rival Ibrahim Zakari who garnered 20 votes at the state party’s primary election conducted at the National Youths Service Corps (NYSC) orientation camp along Mani road Katsina. Before the voting commenced, both contestants, Engineer Muhammad Nura Khalil and Ibrahim Zakari had the opportunity to exchange greetings with the delegates. Dr Yusuf Ibrahim, the Electoral Committee Chairman, after the conclusion of the voting and counting of votes announced the results declaring Engineer Muhammad Nura Khalil as the winner of the contest. He said 1,154 delegates drawn from the 34 LGAs of the state participated in the primary elections, describing the exercise as free and fair. Ibrahim commended the delegates for the maturity exhibited during and after the exercise and charged them to join hands together to ensure that the party wins at the forthcoming general elections in 2023. However, Zakari during the exercise announced his withdrawal from the primary elections alleging irregularities and conspiracy.